<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;">Installing the Homebrew</span></font></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">Website: </span><a style="font-size: 18px;" href="https://brew.sh/">https://brew.sh/</a></div><div># To install the brew</div><div>=&gt; /usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install</a>)"</div><div><br /></div><div># To install a package</div><div>=&gt; brew install wget</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">Installing the JIRA (Atlassian)</span></div><div><br /></div><div>Website: <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/download">https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/download</a></div><div>Version: atlassian-jira-software-7.7.0.tar</div><div><br /></div><div>Requirements:</div><div>1. Java8 JDK and setup the JAVA_HOME:</div><div>=&gt; JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_151.jdk/Contents/Home</div><div>=&gt; export JAVA_HOME</div><div>=&gt; java -version</div><div>java version "1.8.0_151"</div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_151-b12)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.151-b12, mixed mode)</span></div><div><br /></div><div>2. Set the JIRA_HOME environment:</div><div>  =&gt; JIRA_HOME=<span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">/Volumes/Data/KFH/KFH_Projects/Dev-Ops/JIRA</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">  =&gt; export JIRA_HOME</span></div><div><br /></div><div>3. Go to the folder where you extracted the JIRA:</div><div>=&gt; cd /Users/khasanov/MAC_Software/DevOps/Atlassian/atlassian-jira-software-7.7.0-standalone</div><div># Run the “start-jira.sh”</div><div>=&gt; bin/start-jira.sh</div><div><br /></div><div># By default the JIRA uses the Port 8080 </div><div># Visit <a href="http://localhost:8080">http://localhost:8080</a> and follow the instruction</div><div>Admin User: khasanov</div><div>Password: Hydrogen3</div><div># The installation will set the JIRA_HOME as you asked.</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></en-note>